{
  "texts": [
    "The encoder E ω maps irregularly sampled spatio-temporal inputs u 0:L-1 ∈ R |X |×L×c -observed at |X | spatial locations over L time steps with c physical channels-into a structured latent representation Z 0:L-1 ∈ R M ×L×d.",
    "The generative model P θ then autoregressively predicts future latent states in a tokenwise fashion, and the decoder D ψ maps the generated latents back into the physical domain.",
    "The full process for a one-step prediction can be summarized as:",
    "Here, M is the number of spatial latent tokens per state Z and d the latent embedding dimension.",
    "The generative model can be repeatedly applied to roll out predictions autoregressively over a horizon of T steps."
  ]
}